Key Match Events: England won by 6 wickets with 4 balls remaining.
Pre-Game Insights: Seventeen years later, England make their return to Pakistan.
Hales recall may mark start of new era for England, as Pakistan look to bounce back from Asia Cup.
Pakistan captain Babar Azam emphasized Pakistan’s focus on improving their powerplay performance.

The pitch at the National Stadium looks very hard, although the England players who have featured here in the PSL say it is likely to skid through. The weather is set to be hot and humid, and the crowd is set to be packed.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The teams will observe a minute's silence before the first T20I, in memory of Queen Elizabeth II and victims of the floods in Pakistan.
